            "text": "Performance Benchmarks and Optimization Techniques"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benchmark the model under realistic workloads to identify bottlenecks. Use tools like NVIDIA Nsight Systems to profile GPU utilization and adjust batch sizes accordingly. Implement caching for frequent queries and consider model parallelism for multi-GPU setups. Regularly update drivers and libraries to leverage the latest FP8 optimizations, and monitor metrics like p99 latency to ensure consistent performance."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deployment Best Practices for Production"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deploy the model in a containerized environment (e.g., Docker) for scalability and reproducibility. Set up auto-scaling based on API load, and use load balancers to distribute traffic evenly. Implement robust logging and alerting for anomalies, and conduct A/B testing when rolling out updates. Finally, document API specifications clearly, including rate limits and error codes, to streamline integration for downstream teams."
